Q1.  Create pfile from spfile to location '/home/oracle/init<sid.ora>'
    SQL> show parameter spfile;

    NAME				     TYPE	 VALUE
------------------------------------ ----------- ------------------------------
    spfile				     string	 /u01/app/oracle/product/19.0.0
						 /dbhome_1/dbs/spfileprod1.ora
    SQL> create pfile='/home/oracle/initprod1.ora'from spfile;

    File created.
Q2.  Create password file with sys password as oracle1
	cd /u01/app/oracle/product/19.0.0/dbhome_1/dbs
	ll
	[oracle@localhost dbs]$ orapwd file=oraad1

	Enter password for SYS: 
	[oracle@localhost dbs]$ 
	[oracle@localhost dbs]$ ll
Q3. Create parameterfile in different location /u01 & start the DB to up and running condition.
	create pfile='/u02/initprod1.ora'from spfile;
	File created.
	SQL> startup pfile='/u02/initprod1.ora';
  	ORACLE instance started.

	Total System Global Area 1090518112 bytes
	Fixed Size		    8895584 bytes
	Variable Size		  738197504 bytes
	Database Buffers	  335544320 bytes
	Redo Buffers		    7880704 bytes
	Database mounted.
	Database opened.
Q4.	How to check all parameters associated with database?
	SQL> show parameter;
Q5.	How to change specific parameters with Scope=both/spfile/memory?
	sql> alter system set parameter name scope=spfile/memory/both;
Q6. How to check which parameter files required DB bounce for the changes to get reflected?


